				\begin{document}$$\eta $$\end{document} of the EM cluster. TRT-only tracks, i.e. tracks with less than four silicon hits, are extrapolated from the last measurement point. They are retained at this early stage as they are used later in the reconstruction chain to reconstruct photon conversions. Clusters without any associated tracks with silicon hits are eventually considered as photons and are not used to reconstruct prompt-electron candidates. TRT-only tracks have to pass the same requirement for the difference in ϕ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
