				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\phi $$\end{document} positions of the cluster barycentre in the local coordinate system of the calorimeter. Including the cluster barycentre position allows a correction to be made for the larger lateral energy leakage for particles that hit a cell close to the edge and for the variation of the response as a function of the particle impact point with respect to the calorimeter absorbers.

