				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$|\eta |<2$$\end{document}. The distributions of the lateral shower shapes are not well modelled by the GEANT4-based simulation of the detector: in comparison to predictions of the MC simulation, most shower shapes in data are wider and centred at values closer to the background distributions. These effects lead to higher efficiencies in MC simulation. FHT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
