				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sim $$\end{document}5%. Most of this improvement is in the low-ET\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E_{\mathrm {T}}$$\end{document} range, where the electron reconstruction efficiency increases by more than ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sim $$\end{document}7%. This constitutes a significant gain for important measurements such as the determination of Higgs boson properties in the channel H→ZZ∗→4ℓ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
